{SECT 0 {EXCHG {PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 57 "restart; with(pl
ots): with(DEtools): with(LinearAlgebra):" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 
233 "Define the Bonhoeffer-van der Pol oscillator. Here x represents t
he voltage V, y the resistance R and z the phase omega t. The forcing \+
A + B * cos(omega t) is the membrane current, with A the DC-bias and a
n AC current B*cos(omega t)." }{TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 238 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 51 "f := (
x, y, z) -> x - 1/3 * x^3 - y + A + B*cos(z):" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}
{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 35 "g := (x, y, z) -> x / 5 - 3/10 \+
* y:" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 24 "h \+
:= (x, y, z) -> omega:" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 237 43 "eq1 := diff(x(t), t) = f(x(t), y(t), z(t));" }
{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 43 "eq2 := di
ff(y(t), t) = g(x(t), y(t), z(t));" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "
> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 43 "eq3 := diff(z(t), t) = h(x(t), y(t), z(t))
;" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 21 "sys :
= eq1, eq2, eq3:" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 297 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 298 "" 0 "" {TEXT 239 32 "Make this system non-
autonomous." }{TEXT 239 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 24 "subs(z(t)=omega*t, eq1);
" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 4 "eq2;" }
{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 0 "" }}
{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 105 "It is possible to combine this into o
ne non-autonomous second-order differential equation by noting that " 
}}{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 0 "" }}{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 21 "x
 = 5 dy / dt + 3/2 y" }}{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 0 "" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 300 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 -1 34 "x(t) = simplify(solve(eq2, x(t))
);" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 300 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 37 "
expand(subs(\{%, z(t)=omega*t\}, eq1));" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 300 "> " 0 ""
 {MPLTEXT 1 0 22 "(lhs(%)-rhs(%))/5 = 0;" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 297 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 298 "" 0 "" {TEXT 239 94 "For the system withou
t forcing, find all three the fixed points and determine their stabili
ty." }{TEXT 239 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 15 "A := 0; B := 0;" }{MPLTEXT 1 
237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 47 "fp := solve(\{f(x,y,
0) = 0, g(x,y,0)=0\}, \{x,y\});" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 59 "J := VectorCalculus:-Jacobian([f(x,y,
0), g(x,y,0)], [x,y]);" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 296 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 42 "fp[1]; evalf(Eigenvalues(subs(fp[1], J)));" }
{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 42 "f
p[2]; evalf(Eigenvalues(subs(fp[2], J)));" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 42 "fp[3]; evalf(Eigenvalues
(subs(fp[3], J)));" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 297 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 32 "So there are three fi
xed points:" }{TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}
{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 25 "(-1, -2/3): stable spiral" }{TEXT 238 
0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 26 "(0, 0): saddle fixed point" }
{TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 23 "(1, 2/3): stable spir
al" }{TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 0 "" }}{PARA 301 "" 0 "" {TEXT 229 54 "Can
 the system with A=0 and B=0 show chaotic behavior?" }{TEXT 229 0 "" }
}{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
230 0 "" }}{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 312 "With A=0 and B=0 this syst
em is a continuous two-dimensional ODE. By the existence and uniquenes
s theorem, different trajectories do not intersect in two dimensions. \+
Assuming that the trajectory is confined to a bounded domain, this mea
ns that the trajectory either settles in a fixed point or in a limit c
ycle (" }{TEXT 230 81 "by the Poincare-Bendixson theorem). So there is
 no chaos possible in this system." }{TEXT 230 0 "" }}{PARA 299 "" 0 "
" {TEXT 230 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 
298 "" 0 "" {TEXT 239 51 "For which range of A are there three fixed p
oints? " }{TEXT 239 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 9 "A := 'A';" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" 
}}}{EXCHG {PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 58 "fp := allvalues(solve
(\{f(x,y,0) = 0, g(x,y,0)=0\}, \{x,y\}));" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 300 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 98 "xfp1 := simplify(subs(fp[1
],x)); xfp2 := simplify(subs(fp[2],x)); xfp3 := simplify(subs(fp[3],x)
);" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 302 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 -1 98 
"yfp1 := simplify(subs(fp[1],y)); yfp2 := simplify(subs(fp[2],y)); yfp
3 := simplify(subs(fp[3],y));" }{MPLTEXT 1 -1 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 115 "plot([xfp1, xfp2, xfp3, yfp1, yfp2, \+
yfp3], A=-1..1, legend=[\"x-fp1\", \"x-fp2\", \"x-fp3\", \"y-fp1\", \"
y-fp2\", \"y-fp3\"]);" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 297 "" 0 "
" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 112 "From the graph it \+
can be seen that the x-coordinate of fp1 annihilates fp3. Let us see f
or which A this happens:" }{TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
238 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 31 "Avals := sol
ve(xfp1 = xfp3, A);" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 299 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 230 0 "" }}{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 175 "This seems to be not
 correct, as it should only be one value. However we may be lucky and \+
have found the other connection point as well. Substituting the soluti
ons gives that " }{TEXT 230 0 "" }}{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 0 "" }}
}{EXCHG {PARA 300 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 47 "simplify(subs(A=Avals[1],
 [xfp1, xfp2, xfp3]));" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 303 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 -1 47 "simplify(subs(A=Avals[1], [yfp1, yfp2, yfp3]));" }
{MPLTEXT 1 -1 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 0 "" }}{PARA 
299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 43 "A=2/27 sqrt(3) is when fp2 annihilates fp3."
 }{TEXT 230 0 "" }}{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
300 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 47 "simplify(subs(A=Avals[2], [xfp1, xfp2, \+
xfp3]));" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 303 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 -1 47 "s
implify(subs(A=Avals[2], [yfp1, yfp2, yfp3]));" }{MPLTEXT 1 -1 0 "" }}
}{EXCHG {PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 0 "" }}{PARA 304 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
43 "A=-2/27 sqrt(3) is when fp1 annihilates fp3" }{TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 304 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 304 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 304 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 66 "Concluding, there are three fixed point
s for  -2/27 sqrt(3) < A < " }{TEXT -1 12 "2/27 sqrt(3)" }{TEXT -1 0 "
" }}{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 305 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 201 0 "" }}{PARA 306 "" 0 "" {TEXT 223 36 "Plot trajectory in (x
,y) phase-space" }{TEXT 223 0 "" }}{PARA 305 "" 0 "" {TEXT 201 0 "" }}
}{EXCHG {PARA 307 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 202 19 "A := 0; omega := 1;" }
{MPLTEXT 1 202 0 "" }}{PARA 307 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 202 10 "B := 0.25
;" }{MPLTEXT 1 202 0 "" }}{PARA 307 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 202 29 "ic :=
 x(0)=0, y(0)=1, z(0)=0;" }{MPLTEXT 1 202 0 "" }}{PARA 307 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 202 67 "sol := dsolve(\{sys,ic\}, [x(t),y(t),z(t)], type=nu
meric, maxfun=-1);" }{MPLTEXT 1 202 0 "" }}{PARA 307 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 202 118 "odeplot(sol,[x(t), y(t)], 500..1000, labels=[\"x\"
, \"y\"], numpoints=40000, color=blue, axes=normal, view=[-2..2,-2..2]
);" }{MPLTEXT 1 202 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 0 "" }}
{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 135 "The trajectory settles in a period-2 \+
trajectory. Note that for both at B=0.24 and B=0.26 the solution orbit
s around another fixed point" }{TEXT 230 0 "" }}{PARA 299 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 230 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 298 
"" 0 "" {TEXT 239 94 "Vary B and analyze behavior by creating a strobo
scopic Poincare section (fixed time intervals)" }{TEXT 239 0 "" }}
{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
238 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 30 "Stroboscopic Poincare secti
on " }{TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 308 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 -1 30 "A := 0; B := 0.39; omega := 1;" 
}{MPLTEXT 1 -1 0 "" }}{PARA 300 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 35 "ic := x(0) \+
= 0, y(0) = 1, z(0) = 0;" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 309 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 28 "N:=5000; dt := evalf(2*Pi); " }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}
{PARA 309 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 40 "timesteps := Array(1..N, i -> (i-
1)*dt):" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 309 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 86 "sol
_arr := dsolve(\{sys,ic\},[x(t),y(t),z(t)], type=numeric,maxfun=-1,out
put=timesteps):" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 309 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 20 "soldd:=sol_arr[2,1]:" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 309 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 21 "xx := soldd[1..N, 2]:" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 
309 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 21 "yy := soldd[1..N, 3]:" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 
"" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 36 "pp := seq([xx[i], yy[i]], \+
i=100..N):" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 
16 "pointplot([pp]);" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 299 "" 0 ""
 {TEXT 230 0 "" }}{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 230 44 "The system is chaoti
c for 0.31 <= B <= 0.39." }{TEXT 230 0 "" }}{PARA 299 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
230 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 298 "" 0 "
" {TEXT 239 43 "Calculate the Lyapunov exponent for B=0.38." }{TEXT 
239 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 296 "> " 0
 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 10 "B := 0.38;" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 38 "Sta
rt from a point on the attractor..." }{TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 
"" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 35 "ic \+
:= x(0) = 0, y(0) = 1, z(0) = 0;" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> \+
" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 16 "N:=2; dt := 50; " }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}
{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 40 "timesteps := Array(1..N, i -> (
i-1)*dt):" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 
86 "sol_arr := dsolve(\{sys,ic\},[x(t),y(t),z(t)], type=numeric,maxfun
=-1,output=timesteps):" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 237 20 "soldd:=sol_arr[2,1]:" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 
296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 18 "x0 := soldd[2, 2];" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 
0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 18 "y0 := soldd[2, 3];" }
{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}
{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 37 "Calculate trajectory and reference..."
 }{TEXT 238 0 "" }}{PARA 297 "" 0 "" {TEXT 238 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 37 "ic := x(0) = x0, y(0) = y0, z(0) = 0;
" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 31 "N:=200
0; dt := 0.05; B := 0.38;" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 237 40 "timesteps := Array(1..N, i -> (i-1)*dt):" }
{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 86 "sol_arr :
= dsolve(\{sys,ic\},[x(t),y(t),z(t)], type=numeric,maxfun=-1,output=ti
mesteps):" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 
20 "soldd:=sol_arr[2,1]:" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 237 21 "tt := soldd[1..N, 1]:" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}
{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 21 "xx := soldd[1..N, 2]:" }
{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 21 "yy := sol
dd[1..N, 3]:" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 296 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 237 16 "epsilon := 1e-6;" }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 40 "ic2 := x(0)=x0+epsilon, y(0)=y0, z(0)=0;"
 }{MPLTEXT 1 237 0 "" }}{PARA 296 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 237 87 "sol_arr
 := dsolve(\{sys,ic2\},[x(t),y(t),z(t)], type=numeric,maxfun=-1,output
